TASK: Define core data types in notebook-core crate that enforce the platform axioms.

CONTEXT: These types are the foundation of the entire platform. They must be precise, well-documented, and enforce invariants at compile time where possible. See axioms entry for what each entry must contain.

TYPES TO DEFINE:
- EntryId (UUID wrapper)
- Entry { id, content: Vec<u8>, content_type: String, topic: Option<String>, author: AuthorId, signature: Ed25519Signature, references: Vec<EntryId>, revision_of: Option<EntryId>, causal_position: CausalPosition, created: DateTime, integration_cost: IntegrationCost }
- IntegrationCost { entries_revised: u32, references_broken: u32, catalog_shift: f64, orphan: bool }
- CausalPosition { sequence: u64, activity_context: ActivityContext }
- ActivityContext { entries_since_last_by_author: u32, total_notebook_entries: u32, recent_entropy: f64 }
- NotebookId (UUID wrapper)
- Notebook { id, name, owner, participants }
- AuthorId (derived from public key hash)
- Permissions { read: bool, write: bool }

ACCEPTANCE:
- All types derive Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize
- EntryId and NotebookId implement Display, FromStr
- Types compile with serde_json serialization
- Unit tests for serialization round-trips
- Clear documentation on each type explaining its purpose

DEPENDENCY: Requires Task 0-1 (workspace) to be complete first.

REFERENCES: See axioms entry for field meanings.
